So yeah. I'm very comfortable with loving Harry Potter while thinking J.K.Rowling is scum. I easily separate art from the artist, though I do absolutely understand why people have trouble doing so and it's totally fine if that's hard for you.

When I'm reading Harry Potter, I'm not thinking about Rowling's intent. I'm experiencing these events, living their lives. It doesn't matter how much of a tool Rowling is, because she doesn't really matter. The story is what's important.
So because I don't have this visceral emotional reaction to her, no emotional reaction gets transferred to her art. I can enjoy Harry Potter without being guilty about it or disgusted by it.

With J.K.Rowling, I know she's a TERF and I know that's bad and why that's bad and so I have a negative opinion of her. But I don't really have any sort of emotional reaction to her. I'm not disgusted by her views, I just see them as bad and harmful.
